  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Children age 1-17 with buckle fractures of the distal radius and/or ulna. -

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients are excluded if there is any other injury to the upper limb or serious
             bodily trauma that might complicate pain scores.  Children with suspected or proven
             metabolic bone disease, or pathologic fractures are excluded due to resultant
             abnormal bone healing.
